top_comment.text:
Wow, crazy episode. Then again, practically all Bravest Warriors episodes 
start out halfway through a story/mission, and it's up to the viewers to 
figure out what happened before that and/or use our imaginations. It's kind 
of odd that Plum has come back from practically out of nowhere. Last I 
remember, she kissed Chris, took that magical peach pit in his head that 
gave him x-ray vision, broke it, and showed a reference to knowing 
something about the Emotion Lord/future Chris before swimming off. I feel 
sorry for Danny. Both him and Wallow should have love interests. It can't 
just be Chris and Beth as the only couple in this series. However, it was 
nice to see that Danny has a cute sliced bread-making creature friend, who 
I hope will bring him a lot of joy.﻿
